description:
You&amp;#039;ve probably heard of the &quot;Keating 5,&quot; but you might not realize that McCain actually is one of them.  This is a short (13 minute) video that explains what the Keating 5 scandal was all about, what McCain&amp;#039;s part was in it, and how it relates to the current financial mess we&amp;#039;re all in.  The hundreds of billions of dollars that the Savings and Loan debacle ultimately cost was paid for by US taxpayers.  Alarmingly similar to the current situation.

Most of the video consists of clips from official hearings and interviews with the people directly involved with the scandal, so there&amp;#039;s no spin or filtering.  McCain claims the whole ordeal was a case of him being in the wrong place at the wrong time.  I don&amp;#039;t think so.  If it was, it was certainly poor judgment.  Judge for yourself.

You owe it to yourself to spend 10 minutes of your time and watch the video to find out what this is all about.

There are 3 files:  The Quicktime .MOV file is the highest quality.  The MP4 file is high quality, but a smaller image.  The FLV Flash file is good for posting online (Facebook, etc.).
